{"title_page": "2018 Hawaii Bowl", "text_new": "{{short description|College football bowl game}}\n{{Infobox NCAA football yearly game\n| Game Name          = Hawaii Bowl\n| Optional Subheader = 17th Hawaii Bowl\n| Title Sponsor      = SoFi\n| Image              = \n| Caption            = \n| Date Game Played   = December 22\n| Year Game Played   = 2018\n| Football Season    = 2018\n| Stadium            = [[Aloha Stadium]]\n| City               = [[Honolulu, Hawaii]]\n| Visitor School     = University of Hawaii\n| Visitor Name Short = Hawaii\n| Visitor Nickname   = Rainbow Warriors\n| Visitor Record     = 8\u20135\n| Visitor Conference = [[Mountain West Conference|Mountain West]]\n| Visitor AP         = \n| Visitor Coaches    = \n| Visitor CFP        = \n| Visitor Coach      = [[Nick Rolovich]]\n| Visitor1           = 0\n| Visitor2           = 7\n| Visitor3           = 0\n| Visitor4           = 7\n| Home School        = Louisiana Tech University\n| Home Name Short    = Louisiana Tech\n| Home Nickname      = Bulldogs\n| Home Record        = 7\u20135\n| Home Conference    = [[Conference USA|C-USA]]\n| Home AP            = \n| Home Coaches       = \n| Home CFP           = \n| Home Coach         = [[Skip Holtz]]\n| Home1              = 3\n| Home2              = 0\n| Home3              = 21\n| Home4              = 7\n| MVP                = [[Jaylon Ferguson]] (DE, Louisiana Tech) & Kendall Hune (DE, Hawaii)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thehawaiibowl.com/smith-leads-louisiana-tech-past-hawaii-31-14-in-hawaii-bowl/ |title=Smith Leads Louisiana Tech Past Hawaii 31-14 in Hawaii Bowl |website=thehawaiibowl.com |date=December 23, 2018 |accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref>\n| Odds               = Hawaii by 1<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/chalk/story/_/id/25435852/full-list-spreads-every-2018-19-college-football-bowl-game |title=Odds for every 2018-19 CFB bowl game |last=Fawkes |first=Ben |date=December 10, 2018 |website=ESPN.com |publisher= |access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n| Anthem             = \n| Halftime           = \n| Referee            = Greg Sujack (MAC)\n| Attendance         = 30,911\n| Payout             = 1,000,000 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.collegefootballpoll.com/bowl-schedule/2018/|title=2018 Bowl Schedule|author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website=CFP.com |access-date=December 3, 2018}}</ref> \n| US Network         = [[ESPN College Football|ESPN]] & [[ESPN Radio]]\n| US Announcers      = [[Beth Mowins]], [[Kirk Morrison]] and [[Allison Williams (reporter)|Allison Williams]] (ESPN)<br>Kevin Winter and [[Brad Edwards (American football)|Brad Edwards]] (ESPN Radio)\n| Ratings            = \n| Intl Network       = \n| Intl Announcers    = \n}}\n\nThe '''2018 Hawaii Bowl''' was a [[college football]] [[bowl game]] being played on December 22, 2018, in [[Honolulu]], [[Hawaii]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/page/cfpbowls2018/2018-19-college-football-playoff-bowl-schedule |title=2018-19 College Football Playoff and bowl schedule |date=May 2, 2018 |publisher=[[ESPN]] |access-date=July 30, 2018}}</ref> It was the 17th edition of the [[Hawaii Bowl]], and one of the [[2018\u201319 NCAA football bowl games|2018\u201319 bowl games]] concluding the [[2018 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2018 FBS football season]]. This was the first time since 2007 that the bowl was not played on [[Christmas Eve]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.khon2.com/sports/local-sports/2018-hawaii-bowl-to-played-on-december-22nd/1155980736 |title=For the first time in a decade, Hawaii Bowl won't happen on Christmas Eve |website=[[KHON-TV]] |date=May 2, 2018 |accessdate=November 25, 2018}}</ref> Sponsored by the [[SoFi]] personal finance company, the game was officially called the '''SoFi Hawaii Bowl'''.<ref>https://www.thehawaiibowl.com/hawaii-bowl-names-sofi-as-new-title-sponsor/</ref>\n\n==Teams==\nThe game was played between the [[2018 Hawaii Rainbow Warriors football team|Hawaii Rainbow Warriors]] of the [[Mountain West Conference]] and the [[2018 Louisiana Tech Bulldogs football team|Louisiana Tech Bulldogs]] of [[Conference USA]] (C\u2013USA). The teams had faced each other 10 times, with Hawaii holding an 8\u20132 lead in the series; both teams previously were members of the [[Western Athletic Conference]].<ref name=udd/>\n\nThis was Louisiana Tech's first trip to the Hawaii Bowl; it was Hawaii's eighth time in this bowl.\n\n===Hawaii Rainbow Warriors===\n{{main|2018 Hawaii Rainbow Warriors football team}}\nHawaii secured a spot in the bowl with a win on November 17 over the [[2018 UNLV Rebels football team|UNLV Rebels]], ending a four-game losing streak and assuring the Rainbow Warriors of a bowl-eligible winning record, as they reached 7\u20135 with one game left to play.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.staradvertiser.com/2018/11/17/sports/sports-breaking/cordeiro-leads-warriors-to-epic-comeback-over-unlv-into-hawaii-bowl/ |title=Chevan Cordeiro leads Warriors to epic comeback over UNLV, into Hawaii Bowl |first=Paul |last=Arnett |newspaper=[[Honolulu Star-Advertiser]] |date=November 18, 2018 |accessdate=November 25, 2018}}</ref> Hawaii subsequently defeated the [[2018 San Diego State Aztecs football team|San Diego State Aztecs]], ending the regular season with an 8\u20135 overall record, 5\u20133 in conference. The Rainbow Warriors' participation in the Hawaii Bowl was confirmed by bowl organizers on November 28.<ref>https://www.thehawaiibowl.com/hawaii-louisiana-tech-to-face-off-in-2018-hawaii-bowl/</ref>\n\n===Louisiana Tech Bulldogs===\n{{main|2018 Louisiana Tech Bulldogs football team}}\nLouisiana Tech announced their acceptance of a Hawaii Bowl bid on November 28.<ref name=udd>{{cite news |url=https://www.underdogdynasty.com/2018/11/28/18116544/louisiana-tech-accepts-invitation-to-hawaii-bowl-bulldogs-rainbow-warriors-la-conference-usa-mw |title=Louisiana Tech Accepts Invitation To Hawaii Bowl |first=Tanner |last=Spearman |website=underdogdynasty.com |date=November 28, 2018 |accessdate=November 28, 2018}}</ref> The Bulldogs compiled a 7\u20135 regular season record, 5\u20133 in conference.\n\n==Game summary==\n===Scoring summary===\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=HAW|HomeName=LT|state=}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=1:08\n| Team=LT\n| DrivePlays=9\n| DriveLength=44\n| DriveTime=3:04\n| Type=FG\n| yards=24\n| Kicker=Bailey Hale\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=8:20\n| Team=HAW\n| DrivePlays=7\n| DriveLength=71\n| DriveTime=3:21\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=Jason-Matthew Sharsh\n| QB=Chevan Cordeiro\n| yards=24\n| Kicker=Ryan Meskell\n| kickresult=good\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=10:27\n| Team=LT\n| DrivePlays=3\n| DriveLength=51\n| DriveTime=0:32\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=Israel Tucker\n| yards=5\n| Kicker=Bailey Hale\n| kickresult=good\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=4:44\n| Team=LT\n| DrivePlays=7\n| DriveLength=92\n| DriveTime=2:55\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=Jaquis Dancy\n| QB=J'Mar Smith\n| yards=58\n| Kicker=Bailey Hale\n| kickresult=good\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=0:55\n| Team=LT\n| DrivePlays=4\n| DriveLength=65\n| DriveTime=2:05\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=J'Mar Smith\n| yards=4\n| Kicker=Bailey Hale\n| kickresult=good\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=24\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=6:14\n| Team=HAW\n| DrivePlays=7\n| DriveLength=38\n| DriveTime=2:39\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=Marcus Armstrong-Brown\n| QB=[[Cole McDonald]]\n| yards=7\n| Kicker=Ryan Meskell\n| kickresult=good\n| Visitor=14\n| Home=24\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=3:45\n| Team=LT\n| DrivePlays=6\n| DriveLength=65\n| DriveTime=2:29\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=Kam McKnight\n| yards=39\n| Kicker=Bailey Hale\n| kickresult=good\n| Visitor=14\n| Home=31\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=14|Home=31}}\n\n===Statistics===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=Rainbow Warriors\n|R1=0 |R2=7 |R3=0 |R4=7\n|Home='''Bulldogs'''\n|H1=3 |H2=0 |H3=21|H4=7\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Statistics  !! style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Hawaii Rainbow Warriors}}\"|HAW !! style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Louisiana Tech Bulldogs}}\"|LT\n|-\n| First downs || 17 || 23\n|-\n| Plays\u2013yards || 66\u2013226 || 70\u2013453\n|-\n| Rushes\u2013yards || 32\u201358 || 38\u2013168\n|-\n| Passing yards || 168 || 285\n|-\n| Passing: Comp\u2013Att\u2013Int || 17\u201334\u20133 || 19\u201331\u20131\n|-\n| Time of possession || 29:23 || 30:37\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Team !! Category !! Player !! Statistics\n|-\n|rowspan=3 style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Hawaii Rainbow Warriors}}; text-align:center;\"|'''Hawaii''' || Passing || Cole McDonald || 10/20, 85 yds, 1 TD, 2 INT\n|-\n| Rushing || Fred Holly III || 9 car, 57 yds\n|-\n| Receiving || Jason-Matthew Sharsh || 5 rec, 67 yds, 1 TD\n|-\n|rowspan=3 style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Louisiana Tech Bulldogs}}; text-align:center;\"|'''Louisiana Tech''' || Passing || J'Mar Smith || 19/31, 285 yds, 1 TD, 1 INT\n|-\n| Rushing || Jaqwis Dancy || 15 car, 57 yds\n|-\n| Receiving || Teddy Veal || 8 rec, 107 yds\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|https://www.thehawaiibowl.com/}}\n*[http://www.espn.com/college-football/boxscore?gameId=401032066 Box score] at [[ESPN]]\n\n{{2018 bowl game navbox}}\n{{Hawaii Bowl navbox}}\n{{Hawaii Rainbow Warriors bowl game navbox}}\n{{Louisiana Tech Bulldogs bowl game navbox}}\n\n[[Category:2018\u201319 NCAA football bowl games|Hawaii Bowl]]\n[[Category:Hawaii Bowl]]\n[[Category:2018 in sports in Hawaii|Hawaii Bowl]]\n[[Category:December 2018 sports events in the United States|Hawaii Bowl]]\n[[Category:December 2018 sports events in Oceania]]\n[[Category:Hawaii Rainbow Warriors football bowl games]]\n[[Category:Louisiana Tech Bulldogs football bowl games]]\n", "text_old": "{{shor