{"title_page": "American Idol (season 18)", "text_new": "{{short description|Eighteenth season of the American reality show singing competition}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox reality talent competition\n| series        = American Idol\n| logo          = American Idol ABC logo.png\n| season        = 18\n| first_aired   = {{Start date|2020|02|16}}\n| last_aired    = {{End date|present}}\n| host          = {{unbulleted list|[[Ryan Seacrest]]}}\n| judges        = {{unbulleted list|[[Katy Perry]]|[[Luke Bryan]]|[[Lionel Richie]]}}\n| broadcaster   = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n| finalsvenue   = \n| winner-name   = \n| image         =  \n| winner-origin = \n| winner-genre  = \n| winner-song   = \n| runner-name   =\n| last          = American Idol (season 17)\n| next          =\n| year          = 2020\n}}\nThe eighteenth season of the reality show singing competition ''[[American Idol]]'' premiered on February 16, 2020 on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Blanton|first1=Kayla|title=When Does 'American Idol' Season 18 Premiere? The Judges Panel May Look A Little Different When It Returns|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/when-does-american-idol-season-18-premiere-the-judges-panel-may-look-a-little-different-when-it-returns-17891907|website=Bustle|accessdate=May 26, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.mjsbigblog.com/american-idol-2020-will-premiere-in-february-find-out-why-so-early.htm |title = American Idol 2020 Will Premiere in February - Find out WHY So Early!|date = October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Bell|first=Amanda|title=ABC Sets Midseason Premiere Dates for ''Grey's Anatomy'', ''The Bachelor'', and More|url=https://www.tvguide.com/amp/news/abc-midseason-premiere-dates-2020/|work=TV Guide|date=November 21, 2019|accessdate=November 21, 2019}}</ref> It is the third season to air on ABC since the series [[reboot]]; [[Katy Perry]], [[Luke Bryan]], and [[Lionel Richie]] returned as judges despite budget cuts.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Iannucci|first1=Rebecca|title=American Idol Judges Returning for Season 18 Despite Cost-Cutting Buzz \u2014 But What About Ryan Seacrest?|url=https://tvline.com/2019/08/05/american-idol-judges-returning-season-18-katy-perry/|website=TV Line|accessdate=August 5, 2019|date=August 5, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Goldberg|first1=Lesley|title='American Idol' Judges Close Deals to Return for Season 3 on ABC|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/american-idol-judges-close-deals-return-season-3-abc-1229134|website=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=August 5, 2019}}</ref> [[Ryan Seacrest]] continued as show host,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/09/20/ryan-seacrest-returns-as-host-of-iconic-singing-competition-series-american-idol-804113/20190920abc02/|title=Ryan Seacrest Returns as Host of Iconic Singing Competition Series \"American Idol\"|date=September 20, 2019|work=[[The Futon Critic]]}}</ref> [[Bobby Bones]] returned as in-house mentor. \n\nTaping was suspended after the Top 21 were selected, and the contestants were sent home, due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|COVID-19 (coronavirus) pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/television/9338436/american-idol-contestants-sent-home-coronavirus |title='American Idol' Contestants Sent Home Amid Coronavirus Outbreak |date=March 19, 2020 |website=Billboard |access-date=March 21, 2020}}</ref> The show is expected to resume production in late April, with the contestants performing from their homes.\n\n== Preliminary auditions ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Location\n! scope=\"col\"| Venue\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{abbr|Refs|References}}\n|-\n| June 7, 2019\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Nashville, Tennessee]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| C.M.A. Festival Fan Alley \u2013 A.B.C. Summer Fun & Games Activation\n| rowspan=\"25\"|<ref name=\"prelims\">