d, Illinois]]\n| B.O.S. Center\n|-\n| September 8, 2019\n| [[Spokane, Washington]]\n| Grand Hotel Davenport \u2013 Autograph Collection\n|-\n| September 10, 2019\n| [[Detroit, Michigan]]\n| Cobo Center\n|-\n| September 18, 2019\n| [[Nashville, Tennessee]]\n| Nashville Municipal Auditorium\n|-\n| September 21, 2019\n| [[Chicago, Illinois]]\n| Wintrust Arena\n|-\n|}\n* <small>{{note|1|Note 1}} This venue was for registration.</small>\n* <small>{{note|2|Note 2}} This venue was for the audition.</small>\n\n== Regional auditions ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Episodes\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| City\n! scope=\"col\"| Venue\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{abbr|Refs|References}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 1, 2, 3, 4, 5\n| September 30 \u2013 October 1, 2019\n| [[Savannah, Georgia]]\n| Perry Lane Hotel\n| <ref name=\"savannah\">{{cite web|title=Savannah, Georgia|url=https://twitter.com/idolspoilers/status/1177582188432437248|website=Twitter|accessdate= September 30, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"savannah2\">{{cite web|title=Savannah, Georgia|url=https://www.wsav.com/news/local-news/american-idol-brings-auditions-to-savannah-for-its-18th-season/|website=WSAV|accessdate=September 30, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 1, 2, 3, 4, 5\n| October 8\u20139, 2019\n| [[Milwaukee, Wisconsin]]\n| Milwaukee Art Museum\n| <ref name=\"milwaukee\">{{cite web|title=Milwaukee, Wisconsin|url=https://twitter.com/idolspoilers/status/1177582243923075072|website=Twitter|accessdate=September 30, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"milwaukee2\">{{cite web|title=Milwaukee, Wisconsin|url=https://www.jsonline.com/story/entertainment/music/2019/10/09/katy-perry-luke-bryan-lionel-richie-milwaukee-filming-american-idol-auditions/3914912002/|website=JSOnline|accessdate=October 9, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 1, 2, 4, 5\n| October 14\u201315, 2019\n| [[Washington, D.C.]]\n| The Wharf\n| <ref name=\"washington\">{{cite web|title=Washington, D.C.|url=https://twitter.com/idolspoilers/status/1183430084633468934|website=Twitter|accessdate=October 13, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"washington2\">{{cite web|title=Washington, D.C.|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B3kK4aQFh0C/|website=Instagram|accessdate=October 13, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 1, 2, 3, 4, 5\n| November 1\u20132, 2019\n| [[Los Angeles, California]]\n| [[South Park Center (Los Angeles)|South Park Center]]\n| <ref name=\"los angeles\">{{cite web|title=Los Angeles, California|url=https://twitter.com/idolspoilers/status/1177582323132456960|website=Twitter|accessdate=September 30, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 1, 2, 3, 4, 5\n| November 7\u20138, 2019\n| [[Sunriver, Oregon]]\n| Great Hall ([[Sunriver Resort]])\n| <ref name=\"portland\">{{cite web|title=Portland, Oregon|url=https://twitter.com/idolspoilers/status/1183941562285342720|website=Twitter|accessdate= October 15, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== Hollywood Week ==\nHollywood Week was filmed December 2\u20135, 2019, at the [[Orpheum Theatre (Los Angeles)|Orpheum Theatre]] in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mjsbigblog.com/american-idol-2020-judges-auditions-begin-in-savannah-schedule.htm|title=American Idol 2020 Judges Auditions Begin in Savannah (Schedule)|accessdate=December 31, 2019|date=September 30, 2019}}</ref> There were several changes this season. Instead of the usual concepts of Hollywood Week with Lines of Ten, Group Rounds, and Solo Round, this season the 167 contestants faced the Genre Challenge. The contestants chose from genres given, Pop, Rock, R&B, Soul, Country, and Singer-Songwriter, and picked a song and were assessed amongst their group. After all  performed, the judges brought the contestants to stage, similar to Lines of Ten, and made their decision. The Group Round was replaced with a Duet Round, in which the remaining contestants picked a duet partner and their song from a list provided. They were given twelve hours to rehearse including a session with a vocal coach, and later, a stage rehearsal. The judges decided if one, both, or neither moved to the Solo Round for which the remaining contestants performed with a backing band. The Top 40 were flown to Hawaii for a Showcase round to determine the Top 20 advancing to the live shows.\n\n== Showcase Round ==\nThe Showcase Round aired on March 29 and April 5, featuring the top forty performing for the judges and a live audience at [[Aulani]] resort in [[Kapolei, Hawaii]]. The following day, the judges narrowed the number of contestants down to twenty-one in the Final Judgment. The following is a list of the contestants who performed, the song they performed at the Showcase, and if they advanced or not. The placement of Grace Leer and Lauren Mascitti will be determined by a vote.\n\n'''Color key:'''\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"font-size: 90%; white-space: nowrap;\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:cyan; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| Male contestant\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| style=\"background:pink; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| Female contestant\n|-\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| Contestant was chosen by the judges to move on to the Top 20\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| Contestant was eliminated\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; line-height:17px; width:100%; white-space:nowrap\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:05%\"|Order\n! style=\"width:20%\" colspan=\"2\"|Contestant<ref name=\"ShowcasePart1TVLine\">{{Cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2020/03/29/american-idol-recap-season-18-top-20-dillon-james/ |title=''American Idol'' Recap: Did Your Favorite Singers Survive the 'Final Judgment'? |last=Swift |first=Andy |website=[[TVLine]] |date=March 29, 2020 |url-status=live |access-date=March 29, 2020}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:05%\"|Age\n! style=\"widt