8\n! style=\"background:pink;\"| \n| Shevonne Philidor\n| 26\n| [[Orlando, Florida]]\n| New York City\n| \"[[You've Got a Friend in Me]]\"\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Eliminated\n|-\n! 39\n! style=\"background:pink;\"| \n| Dakota Cohen\n| 19\n| [[Hollywood, California]]\n| Los Angeles, California\n| \"[[Ain't No Other Man]]\"\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Eliminated\n|-\n! 40\n! style=\"background:cyan;\"| \n| Shelton Taylor\n| 19\n| [[Bulverde, Texas]]\n| Los Angeles, California\n| \"[[Earned It]]\"\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Eliminated\n|}\n\n==Top 20==\nThe Top 20 performed at [[Pellissier Building and Wiltern Theatre|Wiltern Theatre]] in Los Angeles, California, and solo performances aired in one episode on April 1.\n\n===Solos (April 1)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:60%;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4%;\"| Order\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16%;\"| Contestant\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\"| Song<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=1112827934262345730 |user=RyanSeacrest |title=Tonight's Top 20 setlist! Who are you excited to see? #AmericanIdol |date=April 1, 2019 |access-date=April 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://archive.fo/GLaW0 |archive-date=April 6, 2019 |url-status=live |last=Seacrest |first=Ryan}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1\n| Madison VanDenburg\n| \"[[Domino (Jessie J song)|Domino]]\"\n|-\n| 2\n| Shawn Robinson\n| \"[[Jealous (Nick Jonas song)|Jealous]]\"\n|-\n| 3\n| [[Laine Hardy]]\n| \"[[Bring It on Home to Me]]\"\n|-\n| 4\n| Uch\u00e9\n| \"[[Figures (song)|Figures]]\"\n|-\n| 5\n| Eddie Island\n| \"[[Ho Hey]]\"\n|-\n| 6\n| Evelyn Cormier\n| \"[[Leaving on a Jet Plane]]\"\n|-\n| 7\n| Alyssa Raghu\n| \"[[Ain't It Fun (Paramore song)|Ain't It Fun]]\"\n|-\n| 8\n| Ryan Hammond\n| \"[[You Say]]\"\n|-\n| 9\n| Raquel Trinidad\n| \"[[Lovefool]]\"\n|-\n| 10\n| Logan Johnson\n| \"[[Love Don't Live Here Anymore]]\"\n|-\n| 11\n| Dimitrius Graham\n| \"[[Hello (Adele song)|Hello]]\"\n|-\n| 12\n| Riley Thompson\n| \"[[Jolene (song)|Jolene]]\"\n|-\n| 13\n| Walker Burroughs\n| \"[[How Deep Is Your Love (Bee Gees song)|How Deep Is Your Love]]\"\n|-\n| 14\n| Bumbly\n| \"[[Vision of Love]]\"\n|-\n| 15\n| Ashley Hess\n| \"[[Dreaming with a Broken Heart]]\"\n|-\n| 16\n| [[Alejandro Aranda]]\n| \"[[I Fall Apart]]\"\n|-\n| 17\n| Kate Barnette\n| \"[[Sunday Morning (Maroon 5 song)|Sunday Morning]]\"\n|-\n| 18\n| [[Jeremiah Lloyd Harmon]]\n| \"[[Make You Feel My Love]]\"\n|-\n| 19\n| Laci Kaye Booth\n| \"[[I Want You to Want Me]]\"\n|-\n| 20\n| Wade Cota\n| \"[[All I Want (Kodaline song)|All I Want]]\"\n|-\n|}\n\n===All-Star Duets (April 7 & 8)===\nFor All-Star Duets, contestants were split into two groups of ten. The first group aired on April 7 and the second group on April 8. After each contestant performed their duets, the judges selected seven contestants from each group to advance to the Top 14. ''Idol'' contestants were paired with celebrity singers as their duet partners. The artists who duetted with the first group included [[Jason Mraz]], [[Brett Young (singer)|Brett Young]], [[Shaggy (musician)|Shaggy]], [[Pat Benatar]] & [[Neil Giraldo]], and [[Elle King]]. The artists who duetted with the second group included [[Cynthia Erivo]], [[Lukas Graham]], [[Julia Michaels]], [[Ben Harper]], [[Lovelytheband]], and [[Chris Isaak]].<ref>[https://talentrecap.com/american-idol-s2-celeb-duets/] {{dead link|date=April 2019}}</ref>\n\nBobby Bones served as a guest host for the April 8 episode filling in for Seacrest who missed the taping due to illness.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2019/04/08/american-idol-ryan-seacrest-sick-bobby-bones-host/3398073002/ |title='American Idol': Bobby Bones steps in for ailing Ryan Seacrest on Monday's episode |website=USA Today |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190408215556/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2019/04/08/american-idol-ryan-seacrest-sick-bobby-bones-host/3398073002/ |archive-date=2019-04-08 |access-date=2019-04-09}}</ref>\n\n'''Color key:'''\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"font-size: 90%; white-space: nowrap;\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| Contestant was chosen by the judges to move on to the live shows\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| Contestant was eliminated\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:99%;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10%;\"| Date of airing\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4%;\"| Order\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15%;\"| Contestant\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:18%;\"| Song<ref name=\"DuetsSetList\">{{Cite tweet |number=1114587229429456897 |user=AmericanIdol |title=Get your weekend ALL-STARted with the #IdolDuets lineups! \ud83c\udf1f Watch #AmericanIdol Sunday & Monday 8{{!}}7c on ABC \u2728 |author=American Idol |date=April 6, 2019 |access-date=April 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://archive.is/cvZCT |archive-date=April 6, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15%;\"| Duet partner<ref name=\"DuetsSetList\" />\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:9%;\" | Result<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2019/04/07/american-idol-recap-season-17-duets-eliminations-watch-video/ |title=''American Idol'' Recap: Are the Right Seven Singers Going Live? Watch the Best All-Star Duets and Weigh In |last=Swift |first=Andy |date=April 7, 2019 |website=[[TV Line]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190408040811/https://tvline.com/2019/04/07/american-idol-recap-season-17-duets-eliminations-watch-video/ |archive-date=April 8, 2019 |access-date=April 8, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"10\" scope=\"row\"| Sunday, April 7\n| 1\n| Walker Burroughs\n| \"[[Know (album)|Have It All]]\"\n| [[Jason Mraz]]\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| 2\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Kate Barnette\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| \"[[Heartbreaker (Pat Benatar song)|Heartbreaker]]\"\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| [[Pat Benatar]] & [[Neil Giraldo]]\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Eliminated\n|-\n| 3\n| Riley Thompson\n| \"[[Like I Loved You]]\"\n| [[Brett Young (singer)|Brett Young]]\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced\n|-\n| 4\n| Uch\u00e9\n| \"[[I Need Your Love (Shaggy song)|I Need Your Love]]\"\n| [[Shaggy (musician)|Shaggy]]\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced\n|-\n| 5\n| Madison VanDenburg\n| \"[[We Belong]]\"\n| Pat Benatar & Neil Giraldo\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| 6\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Shawn Robinson\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| \"[[Proud Mary]]\"\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| [[Elle King]]\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Eliminated\n|-\n| 7\n| Ashley Hess\n| \"[[I'm Yours (Jason Mraz song)|I'm Yours]]\"\n| Jason Mraz\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced \n|-\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| 8\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Bumbly\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| \"[[Angel (Shaggy song)|Angel]]\"\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Shaggy\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Eliminated\n|-\n| 9\n| Laci Kaye Booth\n| \"[[Mercy (Brett Young song)|Mercy]]\"\n| Brett Young\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced \n|-\n| 10\n| [[Laine Hardy]]\n| \"[[The Weight]]\"\n| Elle King\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" style=\"background:#555;\"|\n|-\n! rowspan=\"10\" scope=\"row\"| Monday, April 8\n| 1\n| Alyssa Raghu\n| \"[[Issues (Julia Michaels song)|Issues]]\"\n| [[Julia Michaels]]\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced\n|-\n| 2\n| Eddie Island\n| \"[[7 Years (Lukas Graham song)|7 Years]]\"\n| [[Lukas Graham]]\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced\n|-\n| 3\n| Wade Cota\n| \"[[Broken (Lovelytheband song)|Broken]]\"\n| [[lovelytheband]]\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| 4\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Ryan Hammond\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| \"[[Hold On, I'm Comin' (song)|Hold On, I'm Comin']]\"\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| [[Cynthia Erivo]]\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Eliminated\n|-\n| 5\n| Evelyn Cormier\n| \"[[Wicked Game]]\"\n| [[Chris Isaak]]\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| 6\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Logan Johnson\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| \"[[What a Time]]\"\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Julia Michaels\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Eliminated\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| 7\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Raquel Trinidad\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| \"[[Tiny Dancer]]\"\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| lovelytheband\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;| Eliminated\n|-\n| 8\n| [[Alejandro Aranda]]\n| \"[[There Will Be a Light]]\"\n| [[Ben Harper]]\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced\n|-\n| 9\n| Dimitrius Graham\n| \"[[Love Someone (Lukas Graham song)|Love Someone]]\"\n| Lukas Graham\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced\n|-\n| 10\n| [[Jeremiah Lloyd Harmon]]\n| \"[[Time After Time (Cyndi Lauper song)|Time After Time]]\"\n| Cynthia Erivo\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6;| Advanced\n|-\n|}\n\n==Top 14 (April 14 and 15)==\nThe Top 14 performances were taped on April 12, 2019, and aired on Sunday, April 14, followed with the live results on Monday, April 15, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mjsbigblog.com/american-idol-2019-top-14-song-spoilers-what-will-contestants-sing.htm |title=American Idol 2019 Top 14 Song Spoilers: What Will Contestants Sing? |date=13 April 2019 |website=Mjsbigblog |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190413152139/https://www.mjsbigblog.com/american-idol-2019-top-14-song-spoilers-what-will-contestants-sing.htm |archive-date=13 April 2019 |access-date=16 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Color key:'''\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"font-size: 90%; white-space: nowrap;\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#fdfc8f; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| Contestant received the to