 [[Lionel Richie]] returned for their second season as judges. [[Bobby Bones]] returned as the in-house mentor, and acted as guest host for the taped April 8, 2019 episode.\n\n[[Laine Hardy]] from [[Livingston, Louisiana]], won the season on May 19, 2019, while [[Alejandro Aranda]] was the runner-up, and Madison VanDenburg finished in third place. Hardy, who was cut at the Top 50 in [[American Idol (season 16)|season 16]], becomes the third returning contestant to win, after [[Candice Glover]] in [[American Idol (season 12)|season 12]] and [[Caleb Johnson]] in [[American Idol (season 13)|season 13]] and the eighth guy with guitar (GWG) to win in ten seasons.\n\n==Regional auditions==\n''American Idol'' announced in June 2018 that 20 cities would be visited by the ''Idol'' bus, beginning with Orlando, Florida and San Diego, California on August 25. Auditions may also be submitted on the official website, or on Instagram, Facebook, Twitter and TikTok.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8459552/american-idol-audition-tour-stops-2018 |title='American Idol' Announces Auditions in 20 Cities, Including San Diego, Orlando & More |last=Aniftos |first=Rania |date=June 6, 2018 |website=Billboard |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180623232139/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8459552/american-idol-audition-tour-stops-2018 |archive-date=June 23, 2018 |access-date=June 28, 2018}}</ref> During the [[52nd Annual Country Music Association Awards|2018 CMA Awards]], three contestants who didn't enter the competition and didn't audition initially, were given a chance to enter the competition. The contestants were Cameron Lenz, Natalee Spiroff, and Meghan Woods.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://abc.go.com/shows/american-idol/news/updates/american-idol-cma-awards-singing-contest |title=Vote Your Favorite American Idol CMA Contest Finalist Through to Hollywood! - American Idol |website=ABC |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190306043640/https://abc.go.com/shows/american-idol/news/updates/american-idol-cma-awards-singing-contest |archive-date=6 March 2019 |access-date=16 April 2019}}</ref> The winner of that vote was revealed to be Meghan Woods on ''[[Good Morning America]]'' on November 16, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://abc.go.com/shows/american-idol/news/updates/american-idol-cma-contest-meghan-woods-winner |title=Meghan Woods Wins a Golden Ticket to Hollywood! - American Idol |website=ABC |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190523225437/https://abc.go.com/shows/american-idol/news/updates/american-idol-cma-contest-meghan-woods-winner |archive-date=23 May 2019 |access-date=16 April 2019}}</ref> However, Meghan Woods wasn't shown in any episode.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Episodes !! City !! Date  !! Venue\n|-\n| 1, 3, 4, 5 || [[Denver, Colorado]] || October 2, 2018 || [[Wings Over the Rockies Air and Space Museum]]\n|-\n| 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 || [[Coeur d'Alene, Idaho]] || October 14\u201315, 2018 || Hagadone Events Center at the [[Coeur d'Alene Resort]]<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lamberson |first=Carolyn |url=http://www.spokesman.com/stories/2019/feb/28/american-idol-returns-sunday-shining-a-spotlight-o/ |title=\u2018American Idol\u2019 returns Sunday, shining a spotlight on Coeur d\u2019Alene |date=April 3, 2019 |work=The Spokesman-Review |access-date=April 3, 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403063009/http://www.spokesman.com/stories/2019/feb/28/american-idol-returns-sunday-shining-a-spotlight-o/ |archive-date=April 3, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 || [[Louisville, Kentucky]] || October 22\u201324, 2018 || [[Muhammad Ali Center]]\n|-\n| 1, 3, 4, 5 || [[New York City, New York]] || October 29\u201330, 2018 || [[Madison Square Garden]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://abc7ny.com/entertainment/american-idol-contestants-brave-cold-at-nyc-auditions/4576477/ |title=Contestants brave New York City cold for shot at becoming next 'American Idol' |last=Kenyon |first=Sandy |date=April 3, 2019 |publisher=WABC-TV |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403062726/https://abc7ny.com/entertainment/american-idol-contestants-brave-cold-at-nyc-auditions/4576477/ |archive-date=April 3, 2019 |access-date=April 3, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 || [[Los Angeles, California]] || November 8\u201310, 2018 || [[Hollywood and Highland Center]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Hollywood Week==\n\nHollywood Week aired over two episodes on March 24 and 25 at the Orpheum Theater. It featured three rounds: Lines of Ten, Group Round and Solo Round. In the first round, each contestant sang individually, and after ten sang, they gathered in a line. Those who impressed the judges advanced to the next round where the contestants perform in groups of three to five people, singing a song together. The remaining auditionees who passed through the group rounds performed their final solos to advance to the showcase round, held in Hawaii.\n\n==Showcase Round==\nThe Showcase Round aired on March 31, which featured the top 40 performing for the judges and a live audience at [[Aulani|Aulani, a Disney Resort & Spa]] in [[Ko Olina, Hawaii]]. The following day, the judges narrowed the number of contestants down from 40 to 20 in the Final Judgement.\nThe following is a list of the contestants who performed, the song they performed at the Showcase, and whether or not they made the Top 20:\n\n'''Color key:'''\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"font-size: 90%; white-space: nowrap;\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:cyan; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| Male contestant\n| &nbsp;\n|-\n| style=\"background:pink; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| Female contestant\n|-\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6; border:1px solid black;\"| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n| Contestant was chosen by the judges to move on to the Top 20\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4; border:1px