hariot]]\"\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;\"| 10\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;\"| \"[[Somewhere (song)|Somewhere]]\"\n| style=\"background:#FF91A4;\"| Eliminated\n|-\n| Laci Kaye Booth\n| 4\n| \"[[To Love Somebody (song)|To Love Somebody]]\"\n| 9\n| \"[[Open Arms (Journey song)|Open Arms]]\"\n| style=\"background:#B0E0E6\"| Judges' save\n|-\n| [[Alejandro Aranda]]\n| 5\n| \"[[White Rabbit (song)|White Rabbit]]\"\n| 8\n| \"Poison\" {{small|(original song)}}\n| style=\"background:#FDFC8F;\"| Safe\n|-\n| Wade Cota\n| 6\n| \"[[With a Little Help from My Friends (Joe Cocker album)|With A Little Help From My Friends]]\"\n| 11\n| \"[[Shawn James (musician)|Through The Valley]]\"\n| style=\"background:#FDFC8F;\"| Safe\n|-\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ Non-competition performance\n|-\n! Order\n! Performer\n! Song\n|-\n| 16.1\n| [[Gabby Barrett]]\n| \"[[I Hope (Gabby Barrett song)|I Hope]]\"\n|-\n|}\n\n===Week 4: Top 5 - Elton John / Bobby Bones' Choice / Hero Dedications (May 12)===\nThis week, each contestant performed three songs: a pick from in-house mentor, Bobby Bones; a song dedicated to their heroes; and a selection from [[Elton John]]'s catalog.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mjsbigblog.com/american-idol-2019-top-5-to-sing-elton-john-catalog-bobby-bones-picks.htm |title=American Idol 2019 Top 5 to Sing Elton John Catalog, Bobby Bones Picks |last=Santilli |first=MJ |website=MJSBIGBLOG |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510150436/https://www.mjsbigblog.com/american-idol-2019-top-5-to-sing-elton-john-catalog-bobby-bones-picks.htm |archive-date=10 May 2019 |access-date=10 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:99%;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16%;\"| Contestant\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4%;\"| Order\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:21%;\"| Song\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4%;\"| Order\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:21%;\"| [[Elton John]] Song\n! scope=\"col\" sty